# New Workflow Step or Integration — Mandatory Checklist

**Rule:** When you add a **new workflow step** or a **new integration** that adds steps to the designer, you **MUST** follow this checklist. Do not ship a new step or integration without completing every applicable row below. This applies to both “new step type” (e.g. backend enum + executor) and “new integration” (e.g. Slack, OpenSearch) that exposes steps in the left palette.

**Why this rule exists:** We once shipped backend step types (e.g. `CRAWL_START`, `CRAWL_STATUS`, `CRAWL_RESULTS`) that were **not visible** in the workflow designer and had no Output Variables or Test button. Users could not drag them from the left sidebar, configure them, or validate them. This rule ensures that **whenever a new step or integration is added**, it is **always** added to every place that controls visibility, configuration, **Output Variables**, and **Test the step**.

**When this applies:** You are adding or modifying a **new workflow step type** or **new integration** (new value in backend step enum, new step executor, new entry in the designer or Integrations panel). The step type string (e.g. `MY_STEP`) must be **exactly the same** in backend enum, executor, and all frontend locations below.

**Reference template:** Use **OCR_EXTRACT** as the solid reference when comparing completeness — it has full coverage (step-type-reference, Sidebar, ApplicationSettingsPanel, workflowStore, stepOutputVariables, PropertiesPanel, ExecutionsView Request/Response, backend executor + wiring, unit/integration tests). See **`_docs/product/guides/HOW_TO_ADD_A_STEP_TO_THE_LEFT_SIDEBAR.md`** “Reference template: OCR_EXTRACT” table.

**New steps must always be enabled by default in every workspace.** So existing users and any tenant/role (including those with a restricted step visibility matrix) see the new step in the palette without admins having to update the matrix. You **must** do all three: (1) **Frontend** — add the new type to `defaultVisibleStepTypes` in **configStore.ts** and to the rehydration/migration block so persisted `visibleStepTypes` gets it. (2) **Backend** — add the new type to **`StepVisibilityService.STEP_TYPES_ALWAYS_ENABLED_DEFAULT`** (workflow-engine) so when the API returns a restricted list from the visibility matrix, this step is still included. (3) **Frontend** — add the new type to **`alwaysShowInPalette`** in **Sidebar.tsx** so the palette shows it even if the allowed list from the API is stale or missing it.

