## Mandatory checklist — do not skip any row

Before considering the new step "done", ensure **every** row below is completed. If any is missing, the step will not appear in the left menu, or will not be configurable, or will not be visible to existing users.

| # | Location | What to add / verify |
|---|----------|----------------------|
| 1 | **`workflow/micro-services/workflow-engine/src/main/resources/docs/step-type-reference.json`** | Add a step definition object for the new type (name, description, parameters, outputs). This is the documentation source used by the UI and AI features. **All user-facing text must be professional, error-free, and free of spelling mistakes** — see **`step-properties-user-copy.mdc`**. |
| 2 | **`workflow/workflow-designer/src/types/workflow.ts`** | Add the new type to the `StepType` union (e.g. `\| 'MY_STEP'`). |
| 3 | **`workflow/workflow-designer/src/components/Sidebar.tsx`** | Add the step to the correct group in `stepGroups`: `type`, `label`, `icon`, `color`, `description`. Include `stepLabel: template.label` in the drag payload so dropped nodes get a human-readable label. **Labels and descriptions: professional, error-free, no spelling mistakes** — see **`step-properties-user-copy.mdc`**. |
| 4 | **`workflow/workflow-designer/src/store/configStore.ts`** | Add the new type to `defaultVisibleStepTypes`. In `onRehydrateStorage` and in `deserialize`, ensure migration logic merges any new default step types into existing users’ `visibleStepTypes` so they see the new step without clearing storage. **Required so the new step is enabled by default in every workspace.** |
| 5 | **`workflow/workflow-designer/src/components/WorkflowNode.tsx`** | Add the step type to `stepIcons` and `stepColors` so the node shows the correct icon and color on the canvas. |
| 5b | **`workflow/workflow-designer/src/store/workflowStore.ts`** | Add the new step type to **`inferStepTypeFromStepId`**: when `stepId` starts with the step’s kebab slug (e.g. `variables-` → `'VARIABLES'`, `debug-` → `'DEBUG'`), return that type. This ensures the step never collapses to generic TASK after save/load. Load and save must use this as fallback: `type ?? stepType ?? inferStepTypeFromStepId(stepId)`. See **step-type-look-and-feel.mdc**. |
| 6 | **`workflow/workflow-designer/src/components/PropertiesPanel.tsx`** | Add a step-type check (e.g. `isMyStep = formData?.stepType === 'MY_STEP'`) and a **configuration block** with inputs for all parameters the backend expects. Add the step type to the panel’s `stepColors` map. **All labels, placeholders, and help text must be professional, error-free, and free of spelling mistakes** — see **`step-properties-user-copy.mdc`**. |
| 6b | **Previous variables** (when the step has parameters that accept template/expression input, e.g. URL, body, passphrase, input text) | Add a collapsible **"Variables you can use in this step"** block using **`usefulVariablesList`** (fromSteps + globalNames). **Must** follow **`.cursor/rules/previous-variables-ui.mdc`**: show **step name once**, then only the **actual variable names** (e.g. `outputData.text`, `myVar`), not the full `{{stepId.outputData.text}}` in the UI; copy and tooltip use the full `{{...}}` value. Use **`variableDisplayLabel(v)`** for display. Pattern: CHOICE, HTTP, ENCRYPT_DECRYPT in PropertiesPanel. |
| 7 | **`workflow/workflow-designer/src/components/ApplicationSettingsPanel.tsx`** | In the "Step visibility" (or equivalent) section, add a label/entry for the new step type so users can show/hide it in the palette. |
| 8 | **`workflow/workflow-designer/src/utils/workflowValidator.ts`** | Add the new type to the `VALID_STEP_TYPES` array so save/load and validation do not reject the step (e.g. "invalid type … Must be one of: …"). |
| 9 | **Backend** | Backend enum, executor, and execution/transition wiring (WorkflowStateManager, SimpleDbWorkflowProvider, WorkflowRecoveryService). See **`_docs/product/guides/HOW_TO_ADD_A_STEP_TO_THE_LEFT_SIDEBAR.md`** sections 7, 8, 8b. **After changing Java source files, you MUST run `mvn clean compile -DskipTests -q` before restarting** — Maven's incremental compiler can silently use stale bytecode (see **`backend-recompile.mdc`**). |
| 10 | **Output Variables** (required if step writes to context or `outputData`) | In **PropertiesPanel.tsx**: add a collapsible "Output Variables" section (toggle state, table with columns Variable / Type / Description for context vars and `{{stepId.outputData.*}}`). In **`stepOutputVariables.ts`**: add the step type to `getOutputVariablePaths(stepType)`. Pattern: DOCUMENT_LOAD / OCR_EXTRACT / CRAWL_* in PropertiesPanel. See guide section 4a and **`.cursor/rules/new-steps-output-variables-and-test.mdc`**. |
| 11 | **Test the step** (required if step can be validated in isolation — e.g. VARIABLES, OCR_EXTRACT, PDF_EXTRACT, CRAWL_START; configurable steps must have a Test button) | **Backend:** Add test endpoint e.g. `POST .../steps/<step-kebab>/test`, accept step params (and optional variables), run executor or validation, return `{ success, ... }` or `{ success: false, error }`; inject executor as `Optional<XxxStepExecutor>`. **Frontend (PropertiesPanel):** Add state (e.g. `xxxTestLoading`, `xxxTestResponse`, `xxxTestError`), callback that POSTs current params to test endpoint, **"Test Xxx" button** and success/error result UI. Pattern: OCR_EXTRACT / CRAWL_START / PDF_EXTRACT. See guide section 4b and **`.cursor/rules/new-steps-output-variables-and-test.mdc`**. |
| 12 | **Request/Response in Executions** (required for every new step) | **Backend (executor):** Put `request` and `response` in the step result’s `outputData` on every run (success and error). Request = inputs/config used (e.g. stepType, parameters; no secrets). Response = result (e.g. success, payload or error). **Frontend (ExecutionsView.tsx):** Add the new step type to Request/Response section conditions (show + force-show), toggle keys, titles, and step-themed styling. **Must** follow **`.cursor/rules/executions-request-response.mdc`** so Executions > steps show Request and Response like HTTP, AI, RAG, PDF_GENERATE, OCR_EXTRACT, SLACK. Where the response (or request) is tabular (array of objects), use the Grid + JSON toggle pattern per that rule (see VARIABLES and DATATABLE in ExecutionsView). |
| 13 | **Enabled by default in every workspace** | **(1) configStore.ts:** New type in `defaultVisibleStepTypes` and in rehydration/migration so existing users see it. **(2) Backend StepVisibilityService:** Add the new type to `STEP_TYPES_ALWAYS_ENABLED_DEFAULT` so when the step visibility matrix returns a restricted list, this step is still included for all workspaces. **(3) Sidebar.tsx:** Add the new type to `alwaysShowInPalette` so the palette always shows it. See rule above: “New steps must always be enabled by default”. |

