## Cross-references

- **Full step-by-step guide (step in left palette):** `_docs/product/guides/HOW_TO_ADD_A_STEP_TO_THE_LEFT_SIDEBAR.md` — sections 4a (Output Variables), 4b (Test button), 5b (Request/Response), 7–8b (backend wiring).
- **Custom integration (right panel + steps):** `_docs/product/guides/HOW_TO_ADD_A_CUSTOM_INTEGRATION.md` — use when adding a new integration that adds steps.
- **Output Variables & Test button (detailed pattern):** **`.cursor/rules/new-steps-output-variables-and-test.mdc`** — exact UI pattern, stepOutputVariables.ts, test endpoint shape; **must** be followed for every new step or integration where the step produces output or can be tested.
- **Request/Response in Executions (mandatory):** For **every** new step, follow **`.cursor/rules/executions-request-response.mdc`** so Request and Response appear in Executions > steps (backend: request/response in outputData; ExecutionsView: step type in Request/Response sections). For tabular response/request data, use the Grid + JSON pattern (section 5 of that rule). See checklist row 12.
- **Step properties user copy:** When a step has many properties (or any), all user-facing text (labels, descriptions, placeholders, help) must be **professional, error-free, and free of spelling mistakes**. See **`.cursor/rules/step-properties-user-copy.mdc`**.
- **Step type preserved on load:** For **every** new step, add its stepId prefix to **`inferStepTypeFromStepId`** in `workflowStore.ts` (e.g. `variables-` → `VARIABLES`). If the step has a user-facing alias, also add it to **`normalizeStepType`**. See **`.cursor/rules/step-type-look-and-feel.mdc`**.
- **Previous variables UI:** When a step has parameters that accept template/expression input (e.g. `{{variable}}`), add "Variables you can use in this step" and follow **`.cursor/rules/previous-variables-ui.mdc`** — step name once, then only variable names in the list; full `{{...}}` for copy and tooltip.

